headline: Dow Rallies Above 46000 for the First Time
summary: Investors on Thursday ushered the Dow Jones Industrial Average behind a velvet rope and into a new club: The blue-chip index surpassed 46000 for the first time.  Reaching the latest thousand-point milestone took 191 trading days, with the price-weighted Dow pulled upward by  Goldman Sachs’  success and undeterred by  UnitedHealth Group’s  woes.  The index’s plodding ascendance since hitting 45000 on Dec. 4 reflects a stock market that has methodically ground out gains against a backdrop of new tariffs and concerns surrounding the economy.

headline: Why UnitedHealth (UNH) Stock Is Trading Up Today
summary: Shares of health insurance company UnitedHealth (NYSE:UNH) jumped 3% in the afternoon session after the stock extended its positive momentum as the company eased key investor concerns by reporting better-than-feared preliminary Medicare Advantage Star ratings and reaffirming its 2025 earnings outlook.

headline: The ELC Awards $2 Million in Scholarships to More Than 100 Emerging Business Leaders in 2025 Cohort
summary: The Executive Leadership Council (ELC) proudly announces the recipients of its 2025 ELC Scholarships, awarding $2 million in academic support to 102 outstanding undergraduate and graduate students. This year marks the 30th anniversary of the ELC's flagship scholarship program, a transformative initiative that has supported over 1,100 students since its launch in 1995.

headline: Dow Is on Pace to Close Above 46,000 for First Time
summary: The Dow has passed a key threshold in intraday trading.  The blue-chip index is now on track to close above 46,000 for the first time on record.  The biggest contributor to this 1,000 point gain for the Dow has been Goldman Sachs, while stock of insurer UnitedHealth Group has subtracted the most points.
